  "texts": [
    "The two annotators are trained computer scientists who are closely associated with the task of automated fact checking and are familiar with the domain.",
    "The following guidelines were provided to the annotators.Completeness: A list of questions is said to be complete if the questions cover all aspects of the claim.",
    "The ratings were carried out according to the Likert scale of 1-5.Usefulness: Rating the usefulness of questions determines if the questions would help verify the claim.",
    "The annotators were asked to rate the usefulness of questions resulting from the decomposition of claims.",
    "They were instructed to consider implicit aspects of the claim when rating this and were asked to rate according to the Likert scale 1-5."
  ],
